{"lemma":"قَلّابَةٍ","slug":"قَلّابَةٍ","root":"ق.ل.ب","root_slug":"ق-ل-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ق-ل-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n36071","n36072","n36073","n36078"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%91%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n36071","headword_ar":"قَلَابِ","root":"qlb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[as used in the following instance is an attributive proper name like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fajaAri","text_ar":"فَجَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aiqolibo","text_ar":"اِقْلِبْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalaAbi","text_ar":"قَلَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Alter, O alterer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a prov. applied to him who turns his speech, or tongue, and applies it as he pleases: accord. to IAth, to him who has made a slip of the tongue, and repairs it by turning it to another meaning:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA","text_ar":"يَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", he says, is suppressed before"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qlAb","text_ar":"قلاب"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA. [See also Freytag's Arab. Prov. ii. 247.])"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n36072","headword_ar":"قُلَابٌ","root":"qlb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain disease of the heart."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, K.) And (K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A disease that attacks the camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"occasioning complaint of the heart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and that kills him on the day of its befalling him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a disease that attacks camels in the head, and turns it up."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, TA.) [It is also mentioned as an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quliba","text_ar":"قُلِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.] Accord. to Kr, it is the only known word, signifying a disease, derived from the name of the member affected, except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kubaAdN","text_ar":"كُبَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nukaAfN","text_ar":"نُكَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kbd","text_ar":"كبد"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["K","As","S","O"]},{"entry_id":"n36073","headword_ar":"قِلَابٌ","root":"qlb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qil~iybN","text_ar":"قِلِّيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n36078","headword_ar":"قِلَّابٌ","root":"qlb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qil~iybN","text_ar":"قِلِّيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}